wikipedia_page.main: William Craig Bailey (born 6 July 1944), sometimes erroneously written Baillie, is a Scottish former professional footballer who played as a forward in the English Football League for Brighton & Hove Albion, in the Scottish League for Motherwell and Brechin City, in the Irish League for Distillery and in the English Southern League for Cambridge United.
